Stifel Hires Two Managing Directors for Financial-Sponsors Unit

-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 
2011-09-29T21:06:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/stifel-hires-two-managing-directors-for-financial-sponsors-unit.html
Stifel Financial Corp. (SF) , the St.
Louis-based brokerage and investment firm, hired L.J. McKay and
Thomas Prior as managing directors for investment banking in an
expansion of its financial-sponsors unit.  McKay was head of investor relations and fundraising
globally for Quandrangle Group LLC, and Prior was a managing
director in the financial-sponsors group at  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ,
Stifel said today in a statement. They will be based in New York
and will report to Patrick Keeley and Brad Raymond, co-heads of
investment banking.  Stifel said in June it will make a $40 million investment
in Miller Buckfire & Co., a New York-based advisory firm, to
broaden its restructuring advisory business and to offer its
capital markets services to more clients.  McKay and Prior “bring deep client relationships and broad
product expertise in all facets of  investment banking , including
leveraged buyouts, initial public offerings, and strategic
advisory,” Victor Nesi, co-head of the institutional group,
said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Marcinek in New York at 
 lmarcinek3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scheer at 
 dscheer@bloomberg.net . 